				<td colspan="2"><span>Here is the brutal truth about rolling up a character:
<br />

<br />
NOTHING you do with your stat points at the start is going to have a significant impact 30 levels from now.
<br />

<br />
I do not jest nor do I exaggerate.   You can't ruin a character at the character creation screen.  That takes weeks of work.
<br />

<br />
As an example, I offer my roommate - Ryochan, the level 65 druid on Luclin Server.  When we made our characters 3 and a half years ago, this bozo did not put one single point into wisdom.  He is level 65 with 180 AAs and 4K HP and 5K mana unbuffed and he's never even seen the door of Vex Thal, let alone been inside.
<br />

<br />
Trust me on this -- what you do with these points right now just isn't that significant.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
