<br />

<br />
I'm aware of the effect CHA has on critical fails with lull, and the marginal missed note improvement it offers on fizzle adjusted songs... also the less tangible effect it has on charm duration/resist.... but to claim that Charisma can make or break a bard is a heinous overstatement.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">It has been parsed, it has been discussed, it makes a HUGE difference in missed notes, mez, charm, and lull.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I have seen the parses of missed note % done on fizzle adjusted songs and eventhough the evidence is compelling, I cannot recommend equipping a bard with a charisma heavy setup. 
<br />
Is sacrificing some AC and 20-30 HP and some misc stats worth 10 charisma? 
<br />
Perhaps for 1 or 2 slots, but in order for charisma to make a HUGE difference you will have to sacrifice 10-15 slots for a maxed charisma setup.
<br />

<br />
In my opinion, a few less resists and a few less missed notes is not worth giving up 300-500 HP and a load of stats.
<br />

<br />
Since when does charisma effect mez?
<br />

<br />

<br />
Advising a new player that one single stat alone is the be-all-and-end-all of a class is not just misleading, it's straight out wrong.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
